403 Forbidden scenarios: No tests specifically covering forbidden access due to permissions.

recommendations: Add tests to verify caching headers like ETag and Cache-Control on POST responses where applicable.
Add rate limiting / throttling tests to ensure proper handling under high load.

Add an explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenario to differentiate from 503 (service unavailable) when the database or service fails in a non-503 manner.
If GET retrieval tests exist, consider pagination checks in the GET path to complement the POST coverage.
